Former Liverpool star, Mark Lawrenson has predicted the outcomes of Premier League matchday 29 games. Manchester United will host Tottenham Hotspur on Saturday evening at Old Trafford, while Chelsea will face Newcastle United at Stamford Bridge on Sunday. Liverpool will face Brighton in an away Premier League tie on Saturday afternoon and Arsenal will host Leicester City on Sunday evening at Emirates. Providing his predictions, Lawrenson was quoted by BBC Sport as saying: Brighton 0-2 Liverpool
Brentford 2-1 Burnley
Man United 1-2 Tottenham
Chelsea 2-0 Newcastle United
Everton 1-0 Wolves
Leeds 2-0 Norwich
Southampton 2-0 Watford
West Ham 1-1 Aston Villa
Arsenal 2-0 Leicester City
Crystal Palace 0-3 Man City